50501731.review:
[h1]Spoiler free review, with a short and a little longer version (updated on 2nd June 2019, after the Speedrun and Hard Mode update):[/h1]

Buy this game if:

+ you enjoy pixelated, fast faced and challenging videogames;
+ you're fascinated with themes, gameplay, (music i'd say) and features close to the ones shown in Hotline Miami and Deadbolt;
+ if you're looking for a short and memorable action game; 

Don't buy this game if:

- you believe that spending 15$ on a 4-hour long game isn't acceptable;
- you're looking for a Hotline Miami clone;
- you enjoy a simple, straightforward narrative style;

[b]Verdict 9/10[/b]

Dire, detailed, hectic and sharp game, followed by a majestic soundtrack 
Time required to finish the main game: 4 hours
Time required to complete the game at 100%: 10 hours 

[b]Detailed version[/b]

Here's why the game was so appreciated so far (2nd June 2019):

a) [u] The dialogue sytem is innovative[/u], as you can choose between multiple answers by picking one while a "dialogue meter" is depleting itself through time, allowing you to behold and experiment with different dialogues and interactions;

b) [u] Even if the enemy variety isn't remarkable, the game shines when has to display other kinds of situations[/u] with extreme fluidity and ease, allowing the gameplay to be always engaging and fast-paced;

c) [u] the game itself is quite challenging, and even if it doesn't forgive slips and mistakes the checkpoints are never frustrating[/u] so you'll be always allowed to retry those sections that are troubling you in that moment;

d) [u] you can imagine this game as a mixture of the best elements of Deadbolt and Hotline Miami 1[/u] meaning that you can expect a great level design, pictoresque characters paired up with grim, gruesome topics and sequences;

e) [u] a free update added a speedrun mode and a Hard Mode difficulty[/u]; 

Thanks for reading and for bearing up with me, leave a comment below if you have any questions or observations, have an amazing week!!
If you're enjoying this review format you will find more at my curator's page, which i encourage you to join and follow at: https://store.steampowered.com/curator/32344423/
